{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VcNDrG14d35pHQBG8uqZW1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three goals are met. Here's what was wrong and what was fixed:\n\n**Root cause:** `app-user` had write and read permissions on the `/app` vhost but was missing the **configure** permission. RabbitMQ requires configure access to declare (create) a queue — without it, the `queue.declare` AMQP call returns `Access refused`.\n\n**Fix (one command):**\n```\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user '.*' '.*' '.*'\n```\nThis grants `app-user` configure (`.*`), write (`.*`), and read (`.*`) on the `/app` vhost.\n\n**Verified state:**\n- `app-producer` — `1/1 Running`, 0 restarts\n- `/app` vhost — `app-queue` type `classic`, 7 messages (and growing)\n- Cluster — all 3 nodes running (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`), no alarms, no network partitions"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2131,"cache_read_input_tokens":34164,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2131},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"843a5228-d1de-489b-bd20-28d69cd4f583","uuid":"eb0cf8ec-93d3-465a-9572-828ec967454d","request_id":"req_011CcMR8T6Ae61aWBFH7CwLv"}
